=Introduction=
This protocol will strip metal and other bound material (such as protein) from [http://www.qiagen.com/products/catalog/sample-technologies/protein-sample-technologies/purification-kits-and-resins/ni-nta-superflow Ni-NTA resin] and regenerate it for reuse.  This protocol is scalable for any amount of Ni-NTA resin to be recharged.  Thus, amounts will be given as column volumes (CVs), referring to the volume of the resin bed.  For example, for a column containing 5 mL of resin, washing with 2 CVs of H<sub>2</sub>O would refer to 10 mL H<sub>2</sub>O.


=Recharge protocol=
===Strip the resin===
Wash the resin with 10 CVs of [[#stripping buffer|stripping buffer]]

===Wash out stripping buffer===
Wash the resin with 20 CVs of H<sub>2</sub>O

===Reload resin===
Wash the resin with 2 CVs of a solution containing your metal of choice, commonly [[#100 mM nickel sulfate|100 mM NiSO<sub>4</sub>]]

===Wash out excess metal===
Wash the resin with 10 CVs of H<sub>2</sub>O

===Equilibrate in ethanol for storage===
Wash the resin with 10 CVs of [[#20% ethanol|20% ethanol]] and store at 4°C.


